                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.411,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 143193,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has our opinion this morning in case 07-10441, Corley versus United States, which will be announced by Justice Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.411,
                        "stop": 171.24,
                        "byte_start": 143193,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15113,
                            "name": "Anthony M. Kennedy",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/anthony_m_kennedy",
                            "last_name": "Kennedy",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2757,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 572162400,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2757"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32679,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 47100,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/anthony_kennedy_1_3.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10147,
                            "identifier": "anthony_m_kennedy"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.411,
                                "stop": 15.202,
                                "byte_start": 143193,
                                "byte_stop": 166285,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.202,
                                "stop": 25.928,
                                "byte_start": 166285,
                                "byte_stop": 209230,
                                "text": "Federal law has long required that when a suspect is arrested on federal charges, the arresting officer bring him before a magistrate judge as soon as reasonably possible."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.928,
                                "stop": 44.43,
                                "byte_start": 209230,
                                "byte_stop": 283209,
                                "text": "In two cases, McNabb versus United States and Mallory versus United States, this Court has held that if arresting officers violate this law, any confession the suspect may give during the unreasonable delay is excluded from evidence and this is known as the McNabb-Mallory rule."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.43,
                                "stop": 58.644,
                                "byte_start": 283209,
                                "byte_stop": 340052,
                                "text": "In 1968, Congress considered changing the McNabb-Mallory rule as well as overruling our decision in Miranda versus Arizona and it passed 18 U.S.C. Section 3501."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.644,
                                "stop": 66.817,
                                "byte_start": 340052,
                                "byte_stop": 372757,
                                "text": "And the question in this case is whether 3501 did a way with McNabb-Mallory altogether or merely limited its application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.817,
                                "stop": 78.276,
                                "byte_start": 372757,
                                "byte_stop": 418628,
                                "text": "The issue arose here because petitioner Corley confessed to a bank robbery nine and a half hours after his arrest but before being brought before a magistrate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.276,
                                "stop": 88.347,
                                "byte_start": 418628,
                                "byte_stop": 458961,
                                "text": "The Third Circuit held his confession admissible concluding that Section 3501 eliminated McNabb-Mallory entirely, we disagreed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.347,
                                "stop": 92.095,
                                "byte_start": 458961,
                                "byte_stop": 473903,
                                "text": "Section 3501 is not a model of clarity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.095,
                                "stop": 98.017,
                                "byte_start": 473903,
                                "byte_stop": 497622,
                                "text": "Section 3501(a) says that any voluntary confession is admissible in evidence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.017,
                                "stop": 109.2,
                                "byte_start": 497622,
                                "byte_stop": 542344,
                                "text": "But subsection 3501(c) says that no confession shall be inadmissible solely because of delay unless the delay exceeds six hours."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.2,
                                "stop": 121.804,
                                "byte_start": 542344,
                                "byte_stop": 592708,
                                "text": "If subsection (a) meant what it literally said, subsection (c) would be entirely superfluous because (a) would make any voluntary confession admissible regardless of whether they occurred within six hours of the arrest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.804,
                                "stop": 132.475,
                                "byte_start": 592708,
                                "byte_stop": 635444,
                                "text": "Giving (a) its literal scope would also eliminate some rules of evidence as it would make any voluntary confession admissible even if it were, for example, hearsay or protected by attorney-client privilege."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.475,
                                "stop": 143.683,
                                "byte_start": 635444,
                                "byte_stop": 680270,
                                "text": "We therefore read subsection (a) as doing nothing more than attempting to overrule Miranda and (c) is limiting McNabb-Mallory to confessions given over six hours after arrest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.683,
                                "stop": 158.297,
                                "byte_start": 680270,
                                "byte_stop": 738680,
                                "text": "Section 3501\u0027s legislative history confirms that this is what Congress intended and this reading ensures that the federal requirement of presenting an arrestee to a magistrate promptly retains some teeth."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.297,
                                "stop": 164.454,
                                "byte_start": 738680,
                                "byte_stop": 763340,
                                "text": "Now, we vacate and remand so the Third Circuit can apply the proper interpretation of Section 3501."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.454,
                                "stop": 171.24,
                                "byte_start": 763340,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice and Justices Scalia and Thomas joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
